File: According to the statement released by the Central Energy Fund, both 93 and 95 octane will go up by 11 cents. JOHANNESBURG - Bad news for some motorists -- the price of petrol will increase by 11 cents from 7 August.
According to the statement released by the Central Energy Fund, both 93 and 95 octane will go up by 11 cents. READ: The rise and rise of the petrol price Good news for those who drive diesel cars. They'll see a decrease of 14 cents per litre. READ: SA's middle class feeling the squeeze The price of paraffin will decrease by 2 cents. The Central Energy Fund says this is due to the rand/dollar exchange rate.